[[Image:Estonian film foundation logo.png|thumb|160px|Logo]] The '''Estonian Film Foundation''' ({{lang-et|Eesti Filmi Sihtasutus}}) is Estonia's public film funding organization financed from the state budget of the [[Estonia|Republic of Estonia]]. Founded in 1997 by the Estonian Ministry of Culture, the foundation finances and promotes film productions where at least one of the participating producers is an independent Estonian production company. It establishes and develops international film contacts and supports the training of Estonian filmmakers and maintains the Estonian film database.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=IpR0-OrrwssC&pg=PA164&vq=%22Estonian+Film+Foundation%22&source=gbs_search_r&cad=0_1&sig=ACfU3U0_2IJT2VqBj5Sv6yrXDfGUaBZJtw Culture and Customs of the Baltic States By Kevin O'Connor]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=z4yWr9LzBeAC&pg=PA293&dq=%22Estonian+Film+Foundation%22&sig=ACfU3U1BTndiWspgJaNgOyuXlGfI8Obq9w#PPA293,M1 The Film Finance Handbook]</ref>
Estonia is a member of [[European Film Promotion]], [[Media Plus]], [[European Audiovisual Observatory]], and [[Eurimages]].
