A '''pet tree''' is a kind of [[keyring]] or [[mobile phone]] accessory that contains a very small [[cactus]] or [[succulent plant]] in a [[bell jar]]. The plant can be watered and, once it grows too large for the accessory, can be removed so that it may continue growing.<ref>{{cite news |title= Gardens: Grow and Behold|author= Wild, Adrienne|newspaper= [[Sunday Mirror]]|date= 10 December 2006|page=11}}</ref> Pet trees are popular in [[Japan]], but are also available in [[western world|the West]].<ref>{{cite news |title= 10 Wacky Cell Phone Accessories: 4 Pet Tree Mini Live Cactus|author= DeLeo, Jennifer L.|url= https://www.pcmag.com/slideshow_viewer/0,3253,l%253D213921%2526a%253D213923%2526po%253D4,00.asp?p=n|newspaper= [[PC Magazine]]|date= 24 August 2007|accessdate=20 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= WPM|author= Katbamna, Mira|url= https://www.theguardian.com/money/2006/may/08/careers.theguardian1|newspaper= [[The Guardian]]|date= 8 May 2006|accessdate=20 June 2011}}</ref>

